PHILOSOPHY COVENANT

Any use, fork, or derivative of Marea must preserve the following principles
that are inseparable from the spirit of this software:

  1. ABSOLUTE PRIVACY — No user data may ever leave the user's device.
     No analytics, telemetry, tracking pixels, or external API calls
     that process personal information are permitted.

  2. NO MONETIZATION OF VULNERABILITY — Marea must never be used as a
     vehicle to profit from people in crisis, sensory overload, or
     neurological distress. No paywalls on core therapeutic features.
     The official Marea application is, and shall always remain, free
     of charge (gratis) for every end user. Charging money for access
     to Marea or any derivative of it is a violation of this covenant.

  3. ACCESSIBILITY FIRST — The WCAG 2.1 AA minimum standard is a floor,
     not a ceiling. Any derivative must maintain or improve accessibility.

  4. OPEN SOURCE FOREVER — Any modified version distributed publicly or
     run as a network service must publish its source code under AGPL-3.0.

  5. NO WEAPONIZATION, NO HARM — Marea (including its facial-perception,
     gesture-detection, and neurofeedback components) may never be used,
     adapted, or integrated into:
       - weapons, weapons targeting, or any military or paramilitary
         application, offensive or defensive;
       - mass surveillance, biometric tracking, or any system designed
         to identify, profile, or locate people without their free and
         informed consent;
       - any product, robot, or autonomous system whose purpose or
         foreseeable effect is to physically or psychologically harm,
         coerce, or endanger a human being;
       - any system designed to cause harm between humans and robots,
         or between robots themselves, including autonomous systems
         built to injure, disable, or destroy one another where doing
         so risks human safety.
     This technology was built to hold the most vulnerable — it may
     never be turned into an instrument of harm against anyone, human
     or machine acting on behalf of humans.

Violations of this covenant constitute a breach of the license terms.
